<HEADLINE>
<P>
BROWN'S RETURN PRESERVES VICTORY FOR LOS AMIGOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eddie Brown returned an onsides kickoff attempt 55 yards for a touchdown with 1 
minute 32 seconds left to play, preserving Los Amigos High School's 35-27 
victory over Bolsa Grande in a Garden Grove League game Thursday night at 
Garden Grove High. 
</P>
<P>
Marcus Wilson's 10-yard scoring run brought Bolsa Grande to within one point at 
28-27, but quarterback Bryan Taylor was sacked on his two-point conversion 
attempt by Los Amigos' Seilala Faamausili. 
</P>
<P>
Los Amigos (3-2, 1-1 in league) kept the ball on the ground, attempting only 
four passes and completing none. 
</P>
<P>
Derek Ragsdale gained 111 yards in 22 carries, including an 11-yard scoring run 
in the third quarter, and returned an interception 50 yards for a first-half 
touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
Bolsa Grande (1-4, 1-2) was led by Maurice Wilson, who gained 199 yards in 24 
carries and scored on runs of two and 32 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Pete Gomez and Faamausili accounted for Los Amigos' other scores on runs of 20 
and one yard. SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
<CORRECTION-DATE>
<P>
October 6, 1990, Saturday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</CORRECTION-DATE>
<CORRECTION>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
<P>
Los Amigos football -- In Friday's edition of The Times, Los Amigos' football 
player Eddie Benson, who returned an on-sides kickoff for a touchdown, was 
misidentified. 
</P>
</CORRECTION>
