<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: SUWARA COACHES 400TH VICTORY FOR AZTEC WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rudy Suwara coached his 400th women's volleyball match victory at San Diego 
State Thursday as the Aztecs defeated Cal Poly San Luis Obispo, 15-8, 15-10, 
15-6. 
</P>
<P>
His first women's victory at SDSU was Oct. 8, 1976, and 10 years ago Thursday, 
he won his 100th match. 
</P>
<P>
His women's record at SDSU is 400-185-3. 
</P>
<P>
Including four years of coaching men at UC Santa Barbara and five years with 
the SDSU men's team, he has a record of 564-284-7. 
</P>
<P>
"I've been lucky to be at a real good school with a lot of support," Suwara 
said earlier this week. "And I've been lucky enough to have a lot of wonderful 
players over the years." 
</P>
<P>
Freshman Stephanie Riley (Patrick Henry) had six kills with a .625 hitting 
percentage. Shannon Mathew had seven kills. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU is 11-6, Cal Poly SLO 7-12. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Top-seeded Hans Hoegstedt of Point Loma Nazarene College lost to Azusa 
Pacific's Greg Johnson, 7-5, 7-5, in the final of the Rolex NAIA 
Intercollegiate Tennis Championships at Costa Mesa Tennis Club. 
</P>
<P>
Hoegstedt reached the final by defeating PLNC teammate John Norton, 6-2, 6-3, 
in the semifinals. 
</P>
