<P>
MOORPARK COACH EARNS 200TH WRESTLING WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John Keever, the Moorpark College wrestling coach, picked up his 200th career 
dual-meet victory earlier this week when Moorpark beat Golden West, 22-14. 
</P>
<P>
Keever, in his 22nd year at Moorpark, has earned all 200 wins with the Raiders. 
He has a career record of 200-99-4. 
</P>
<P>
Last season, the Raiders finished second in the state meet, marking the best 
finish by a Moorpark team coached by Keever. 
</P>
<P>
Robby Cook, at 142 pounds, and Phil Guerrero, at 190, both won on major 
decisions to help Keever achieve his landmark victory Wednesday. 
</P>
