<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLIDAY GIFT OF PARKING NEAR MALL TO CEASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SHAWN HUBLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
You'd better not cry, you'd better not pout and you'd better not park on the 
residential streets around the South Bay Galleria during the Christmas shopping 
season this year, or Santa will be putting a naughty surprise on your 
windshield. 
</P>
<P>
Hoping to head off a seasonal parking crunch in the neighborhoods around the 
popular Redondo Beach shopping mall, the City Council this week created a 
temporary permit-parking zone on Kingsdale, Firmona and Condon avenues that 
would prohibit non-resident parking from Nov. 15 until Dec. 31. 
</P>
<P>
Affected are the 1800 and 1900 blocks of Kingsdale and Firmona avenues and the 
1900 block of Condon Avenue between 10 a.m. and 8 p.m. Commercial areas of the 
blocks would be exempt from the restriction and will be posted. 
</P>
<P>
Doug Anderson, who owns a home in the area, told the council that temporary 
restrictions were much-needed in his neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
"The parking there is already a problem," he said, and becomes much worse 
during the shopping season. 
</P>
<P>
"It's not only the shoppers," Councilman Terry Ward said. "The employees also 
were coming into the area and parking on the residential streets." 
</P>
<P>
Last year, the neighborhood petitioned the city for the district, complaining 
that they could not get into their driveways because the streets were so 
crammed with overflow Galleria parking. SHAWN HUBLER 
</P>
</TEXT>
