<P>
FALLEN ANGEL: If anyone could gloat over apparent demotion of Angels General 
Manager Mike Port (C1), it's former Angel Bob Boone. . . . The popular catcher, 
once named the team's co-MVP, jumped to Kansas City in 1988, signing for only 
$1 more than his Angels salary. Team owner Gene Autry, shaken by Boone's 
departure, praised Port with faint damns: "I think Mike could be a little more 
friendly with people he deals with." 
</P>
<P>
.. . But Boone, who still lives in Orange County, refuses to crow: "I don't 
hate Mike Port. I'm not sure I can get a deal done with him." . . . And Boone 
soon will be dealing. He said Thursday he'll be a free agent when the Royals 
set him loose this month, but he's not saying whether he would consider 
returning to Anaheim. Steve Emmons and Mark I. Pinsky 
