<P>
OPTIMISM: Apparently it takes a lot of recession talk before Orange County gets 
scared. . . . Last winter, a survey showed that about one in five county 
households planned to buy a new car. 
</P>
<P>
By late summer, that figure had risen to about one in four, despite a year of 
recession speculation. In fact, more than half of those surveyed in August 
thought they'd be "better off financially" a year hence. Only 8% thought they'd 
wind up worse off. . . . But the jury's still out. Surveys taken after the 
Mideast crisis and federal deficit developments have not yet been tallied. 
Steve Emmons and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
