<P>
CRIME BUSTERS: There is sometimes a trade-off when cities like Anaheim and 
Santa Ana make major commitments to solve violent crimes like assault, above, 
and rape (A1). . . . Lesser crimes involving property may be neglected as a 
result, says Lt. Marc Hedgpeth, commander of the Crimes Against Persons Bureau 
in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
"We are always robbing Peter to pay Paul." 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
