<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NFL; 
</P>
<P>
DID RYPIEN TAKE WRONG OPTION? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The knee injury that has sidelined Mark Rypien could be an expensive one for 
the Washington Redskins' quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
Rypien, who damaged ligaments in his left knee in a game Sept. 23, is playing 
out his option after turning down the Redskins' contract offer worth $700,000 
this season. 
</P>
<P>
Rypien had turned down a three-year, $2.4-million deal that included $600,000 
in incentives. He's playing for $275,000 this season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
