<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
MOTHER HELD IN TEACHER ASSAULT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 6-foot, 240-pound woman was jailed for grabbing her daughter's 64-year-old 
kindergarten teacher by the throat and throwing her to the classroom floor, 
police said today. 
</P>
<P>
Benita McCrae, 30, was being held on $10,000 bail on suspicion of assaulting a 
school official. 
</P>
<P>
Her daughter was turned over to the county Department of Children's Services, 
Detective Gary Barthelmess said. 
</P>
<P>
McCrae took her 5-year-old daughter Thursday morning to Toluca Lake Elementary 
School, where the child was newly enrolled. McCrae told the teacher that she 
wanted to spend the entire day in class with the child. 
</P>
<P>
The teacher, Marjorie Swanter, said she would not allow an all-day visit but 
said the mother could stay for 20 minutes. An argument ensued and, Barthelmess 
said, McCrae "grabbed the . . . teacher by the throat and threw her to the 
ground." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
