<P>
REWARD SET FOR RUMOR SPREADER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An Australian bank today offered an $8,300 reward in an effort to catch the 
source of rumors that the bank was near collapse. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Brisbane-based Metway Bank said he believed the bank had been 
the target of a deliberate and malicious campaign that should not go 
unpunished. 
</P>
<P>
"We do not see why the company should be exposed to this sort of scurrilous 
lies," the spokesman said by telephone. 
</P>
<P>
The reward would be paid for information leading to the conviction of the 
culprits, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Nervous depositors lined up at branches of Metway this week when rumors began 
circulating about the bank's financial health. 
</P>
<P>
The Reserve Bank, Australia's central bank, stemmed the rush Thursday when it 
assured depositors that Metway is sound and that speculation about its 
stability was unfounded. 
</P>
