<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
HEPBURN, FRIENDS ACT NATURALLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW HAVEN, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Hope, Barbra Streisand, Elizabeth Taylor and Shirley MacLaine have joined 
actress Katharine Hepburn in donating items to an art auction Saturday for the 
North American Wildlife Assn. 
</P>
<P>
The association, based in East Lyme, provides the only 24-hour wildlife rescue 
service in Connecticut. 
</P>
<P>
Taylor has donated a signed tote bag. MacLaine is contributing an autographed 
book. An oil painting by Hepburn will be one of 90 artworks auctioned. 
</P>
<P>
Hepburn, who has a home in Old Saybrook, became a backer of the group after it 
rescued a sea bird with a broken wing she had found. 
</P>
<P>
Hope, Streisand and Charlton Heston have donated autographed photos, and actor 
Chad Everett is expected to provide three original poems, said Steve Sosensky, 
an auction organizer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
